{"article_id":"oBe15rI1kRmvg1ep","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":2},{"id":1,"text":"The second Dallas health care worker","depth":15},{"id":2,"text":"who was found to have the Ebola virus","depth":15},{"id":3,"text":"should not have boarded a commercial jet Monday ,","depth":14},{"id":4,"text":"health officials say .","depth":13},{"id":5,"text":"Because she had helped care for Ebola patient Thomas Eric Duncan ,","depth":15},{"id":6,"text":"and because another health worker","depth":17},{"id":7,"text":"who cared for Duncan","depth":17},{"id":8,"text":"had been diagnosed with Ebola ,","depth":16},{"id":9,"text":"the worker was not allowed to travel on a commercial plane with other people ,","depth":14},{"id":10,"text":"said Dr. Tom Frieden , director of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention .","depth":13},{"id":11,"text":"The worker had a temperature of 99.5 Fahrenheit","depth":14},{"id":12,"text":"( 37.5 Celsius )","depth":14},{"id":13,"text":"before she boarded her flight ,","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"he added .","depth":12},{"id":15,"text":"Health care workers","depth":14},{"id":16,"text":"who had been exposed to Duncan","depth":14},{"id":17,"text":"were undergoing self-monitoring .","depth":13},{"id":18,"text":"They were allowed to travel","depth":14},{"id":19,"text":"but not on a commercial plane with other people ,","depth":14},{"id":20,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"Moving forward , the CDC will ensure","depth":13},{"id":22,"text":"that no one else in such a situation travels outside of a closed environment ,","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"he said .","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"The worker is Amber Vinson , 29 , a nurse at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital in Dallas .","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"She was confirmed to have Ebola overnight .","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Now , she will be transferred from the Dallas hospital to Emory University Hospital in Atlanta ,","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"which has successfully treated two other patients .","depth":14},{"id":28,"text":"It is now treating a third :","depth":14},{"id":29,"text":"a male health care worker","depth":15},{"id":30,"text":"who was infected in Sierra Leone .","depth":15},{"id":31,"text":"The first Dallas health care worker with Ebola , Nina Pham , is in `` improved condition , ''","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"Frieden said .","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"It has not been determined whether she will be transferred to another facility .","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"Both Dallas health workers had `` extensive contact '' with Duncan on October 28-30 ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"when he had `` extensive production of body fluids '' such as vomit and diarrhea ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Frieden told reporters in a conference call .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"The risk of exposure to the passengers","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"who were on the plane with Vinson","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"is low ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"since she did not yet have symptoms ,","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"health officials said Wednesday .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"The Ebola virus is not contagious","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"before symptoms set in .","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"Still , the CDC wants to interview all 132 passengers","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"who were on the plane with her .","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"`` Because of the proximity in time between the evening flight and first report of illness the following morning ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"CDC is reaching out to passengers","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"who flew on Frontier Airlines flight 1143 Cleveland to Dallas/Fort Worth Oct. 13 , ''","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"the CDC said in a statement .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"The flight landed Monday at 8:16 p.m. CT .","depth":8},{"id":51,"text":"The woman `` exhibited no symptoms or sign of illness while on Flight 1143 ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"according to the crew , ''","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"Frontier Airlines said in a statement .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"Earlier , Vinson flew from Dallas-Fort Worth to Cleveland on Frontier Flight 1142 on October 10 .","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"The airline said","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"customers","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"who may have traveled on either flight","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"should contact the CDC at 1-800-CDC-INFO","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"( 1-800-232-4636 ) .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"But the CDC statement ,","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"contained in the same news release ,","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"the CDC wanted to speak only with passengers of the October 13 flight .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"The CDC later confirmed to CNN","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"that it is `` only interested '' in the passengers on Flight 1143 .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"The October 13 flight was cleaned thoroughly","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"after it landed ,","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"`` per our normal procedures","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"which is consistent with CDC guidelines , ''","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"the airline said .","depth":11},{"id":71,"text":"After the airline was informed of the Ebola patient ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"the plane was removed from service .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"In a sign of growing concerns about Ebola , President Obama canceled trips to New Jersey and Connecticut on Wednesday","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"to convene a meeting at the White House of Cabinet agencies","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"coordinating the government 's response to the outbreak .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"Vinson ,","depth":9},{"id":77,"text":"who lives alone ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"is in isolation at Texas Health Presbyterian Hospital .","depth":8},{"id":79,"text":"The news","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"that she contracted Ebola","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"cast further doubt on the hospital 's ability","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"to handle the virus","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"and protect employees .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"It 's the same hospital","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"that initially sent Thomas Eric Duncan home ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"even though he had a fever","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"and had traveled from West Africa .","depth":11},{"id":88,"text":"By the time he returned to the hospital ,","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"his symptoms had worsened .","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"He died","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"while being treated by medical staff ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"including the two women","depth":12},{"id":93,"text":"who have now contracted the disease .","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":8},{"id":95,"text":"we have a systematic institutional problem , ''","depth":8},{"id":96,"text":"Dr. Daniel Varga , chief clinical officer of Texas Health Resources , told reporters Wednesday ,","depth":8},{"id":97,"text":"facing questions about the hospital 's actions .","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":99,"text":"Air airport precautions effective ?","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"MUST WATCH Air airport precautions effective ?","depth":7},{"id":102,"text":"04:19","depth":7},{"id":103,"text":"JUST WATCHED UN :","depth":9},{"id":104,"text":"Ebola could be ebbed by year 's end","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"MUST WATCH UN :","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"Ebola could be ebbed by year 's end","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"07:44","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"Dallas doctors try to calm Ebola fears","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":10},{"id":112,"text":"MUST WATCH Dallas doctors try to calm Ebola fears","depth":11},{"id":113,"text":"02:35","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"Medical staff `` may have done some things differently with the benefit of what we know today , ''","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":116,"text":"adding ,","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"`` no one wants to get this right more than our hospital . ''","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"People in the health care worker 's office building were informed","depth":10},{"id":119,"text":"when officials went door to door ,","depth":10},{"id":120,"text":"and also through early morning reverse 911 calls ,","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"officials said .","depth":8},{"id":122,"text":"Seventy-five health care workers in Dallas are being monitored for any Ebola symptoms ,","depth":7},{"id":123,"text":"Varga said .","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"Separately , Dallas County Judge Clay Jenkins ,","depth":11},{"id":125,"text":"who is overseeing the response efforts ,","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"48 other people in the community still are being monitored","depth":10},{"id":128,"text":"after having contact with Duncan ,","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"who was Dallas ' first Ebola patient .","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"Those 48 are asymptomatic ,","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"and Sunday will mark the end of the window","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"in which they could get sick .","depth":10},{"id":133,"text":"The second worker reported a fever Tuesday","depth":9},{"id":134,"text":"and was immediately isolated ,","depth":9},{"id":135,"text":"health department spokeswoman Carrie Williams said .","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"The virus is not contagious","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"before there are symptoms .","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"A preliminary Ebola test was done late Tuesday at the state public health laboratory in Austin ,","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"and the results came back around midnight .","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"A second test will be conducted by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in Atlanta .","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"`` Health officials have interviewed the latest patient","depth":12},{"id":142,"text":"to quickly identify any contacts or potential exposures ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"and those people will be monitored , ''","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"the health department said .","depth":10},{"id":145,"text":"The worker 's apartment and car will be cleaned Wednesday ,","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"Dallas Mayor Mike Rawlings said .","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"An official close to the situation says","depth":7},{"id":148,"text":"that in hindsight , Duncan should have been transferred immediately to either Emory University Hospital in Atlanta or Nebraska Medical Center in Omaha .","depth":7},{"id":149,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":4},{"id":150,"text":"Nurse :","depth":5},{"id":151,"text":"I am 'blessed ' with the best care","depth":5},{"id":152,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":5},{"id":153,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"Nurse :","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"I am 'blessed ' with the best care","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"02:06","depth":7},{"id":157,"text":"Those hospitals are among only four in the country","depth":8},{"id":158,"text":"that have biocontainment units","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"and have been preparing for years","depth":10},{"id":160,"text":"to treat a highly infectious disease like Ebola .","depth":10},{"id":161,"text":"`` If we knew then what we know now about this hospital 's ability","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"to safely care for these patients ,","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"then we would have transferred him to Emory or Nebraska , ''","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"the official told CNN senior medical correspondent Elizabeth Cohen .","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"`` I think","depth":10},{"id":166,"text":"there are hospitals","depth":11},{"id":167,"text":"that are more than ready ,","depth":11},{"id":168,"text":"but I think","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"there are some","depth":11},{"id":170,"text":"that are not . ''","depth":11},{"id":171,"text":"Also Tuesday , National Nurses United made troubling allegations about the hospital ,","depth":7},{"id":172,"text":"claiming","depth":10},{"id":173,"text":"`` guidelines were constantly changing ''","depth":11},{"id":174,"text":"and `` there were no protocols ''","depth":12},{"id":175,"text":"about how to deal with the deadly virus . ''","depth":12},{"id":176,"text":"`` The protocols","depth":13},{"id":177,"text":"that should have been in place in Dallas","depth":13},{"id":178,"text":"were not in place ,","depth":12},{"id":179,"text":"and that those protocols are not in place anywhere in the United States","depth":12},{"id":180,"text":"as far as we can tell , ''","depth":12},{"id":181,"text":"NNU Executive Director RoseAnn DeMoro said .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"`` We 're deeply alarmed . ''","depth":8},{"id":183,"text":"Nurses were told to wrap their necks with medical tape","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"when equipment left their necks exposed ;","depth":9},{"id":185,"text":"they felt unsupported and unprepared ,","depth":9},{"id":186,"text":"and they received no hands-on training ,","depth":9},{"id":187,"text":"union co-president Deborah Burger said .","depth":7},{"id":188,"text":"A Texas Health Presbyterian spokesman did not respond to the specific allegations","depth":6},{"id":189,"text":"but said","depth":7},{"id":190,"text":"patient and employee safety is the hospital 's top priority .","depth":7},{"id":191,"text":"While the Texas hospital deals with its third Ebola patient ,","depth":4},{"id":192,"text":"the situation in West Africa is getting increasingly dire .","depth":4},{"id":193,"text":"A total of 4,493 people are confirmed to have died from Ebola this year , from Guinea , Liberia , Nigeria , Senegal , Sierra Leone , Spain and the United States ,","depth":5},{"id":194,"text":"the World Health Organization said Wednesday .","depth":5},{"id":195,"text":"There could be 10,000 new Ebola cases per week in Sierra Leone , Liberia and Guinea by the end of this year","de